Following is a table showing Indian companies
selling shares through a qualified institutional placement, or QIP, according
to company filings to the  Bombay  and  National Stock  Exchanges.  Indian companies plan to raise a further $5.7 billion* in addition to
the $14.6 billion* they’ve already raised since the start of April 2009.  
